\begin{document}$$ X_ + = \sum\nolimits_{j = 1}^J {X_j } $$\end{document}. Total score X+ is an estimate of a patient’s true score T; this is the expectation of X+ across independent replications of the measurement procedure ([20], pp. 29–30).

Parametric Graded Response Model. The ISRFs of the parametric GRM [26] are defined by logistic functions that have the following parameters:
δjm: the location parameter of the mth ISRF of item j (i.e., Pjm(θ)) on the scale of θ;
αj: the slope parameter or ‘discrimination power’ of item j.

